{"title":"Weapon-tool","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Weapon-tool","type":"markdown","data":"A **weapon-tool** is a type of [tool](/wiki/Tool \"Tool\") in *[NetHack](/wiki/NetHack \"NetHack\")* that functions in the same manner as a [weapon](/wiki/Weapon \"Weapon\"):[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1) a weapon-tool has an accompanying weapon [skill](/wiki/Skill \"Skill\"), can be enchanted under the same rules as regular weapons, and a cursed weapon-tool will weld to the hand(s) of a [hero](/wiki/Hero \"Hero\") or [monster](/wiki/Monster \"Monster\") that [wields](/wiki/Wield \"Wield\") one.\n\n[ ]\n\n## Contents\n\n- [1 Description](#Description)\n- [2 Variants](#Variants)\n  - [2.1 UnNetHack](#UnNetHack)\n- [3 References](#References)\n\n## Description\n\nThe following items are considered weapon-tools:\n\n| Item                                                    | Skill        | Two-handed | Material                  |\n| ------------------------------------------------------- | ------------ | ---------- | ------------------------- |\n| [pick-axe](/wiki/Pick-axe \"Pick-axe\")                   | pick-axe     | no         | [iron](/wiki/Iron \"Iron\") |\n| [grappling hook](/wiki/Grappling_hook \"Grappling hook\") | flail        | no         | [iron](/wiki/Iron \"Iron\") |\n| [unicorn horn](/wiki/Unicorn_horn \"Unicorn horn\")       | unicorn horn | yes        | [bone](/wiki/Bone \"Bone\") |\n\nThere are weapons and tools that have functional similarities, but are not themselves weapon-tools:\n\n- The [dwarvish mattock](/wiki/Dwarvish_mattock \"Dwarvish mattock\") has the same weapon skill and functions as a pick-axe, but is actually considered a weapon outright.\n- [Axes](/wiki/Axe \"Axe\") and [battle-axes](/wiki/Battle-axe \"Battle-axe\") are weapons, but can be [applied](/wiki/Applied \"Applied\") similar to other tools in order to chop down doors.\n- A [tin opener](/wiki/Tin_opener \"Tin opener\") is a tool that must be wielded, and applying the tool will wield it before prompting for a tin to open; a cursed tin opener will also weld itself to a hero's hand.\n- A wet [towel](/wiki/Towel \"Towel\") can be used as an improvised weapon, but has special cases concerning this in the code in order to avoid classifying it as a weapon-tool.\n\nSince weapon-tools also count as weapons, hitting a monster with one breaks the [weaponless](/wiki/Weaponless \"Weaponless\") [conduct](/wiki/Conduct \"Conduct\").[\\[2\\]](#cite_note-2)\n\n## Variants\n\n### UnNetHack\n\n[UnNetHack](/wiki/UnNetHack \"UnNetHack\") adds the [crystal pick](/wiki/Crystal_pick \"Crystal pick\") as a weapon-tool.\n\n## References\n\n1. [↑](#cite_ref-1) [include/obj.h in NetHack 3.6.7, line 189](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/include/obj.h#L189): *`is_weptool`*\n2. [↑](#cite_ref-2) [src/uhitm.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 488](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/uhitm.c#L488)\n\n[![This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.7. Click here for more information.](/images/f/f7/Nh367-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.7. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Weapon-tool - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Weapon-tool\",\"wgTitle\":\"Weapon-tool\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":177460,\"wgRevisionId\":177460,\"wgArticleId\":20656,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Nethack-367 articles\",\"Tools\",\"Weapons\",\"Weapon-tools\"],\"wgBreakFra